Famous Bridal MUA & Educator Naina Goel is here to make sure Moms & Mom-In-Laws steal the show this wedding season! 💕 Get ready to shine because it’s officially #NykaaWaaliShaadi season!

💄 From skin prep to the final glam, Naina shares her personal secrets exclusively with Nykaa Nation:
🧴 Foundation: Maybelline Super Stay Lumi Matte Liquid Foundation in Shade 228
✨ Concealer: Anastasia Magic Touch Concealer in Shade 5
🌟 Loose Powder: Huda Beauty Easy Bake Loose Powder in “Banana Bread”
🎨 Face Palette: Sugar Contour De Force Face Palette in “Subtle Summit”
👁 Eyeshadow Palette: Simply Nam Dawn to Dusk Eyeshadow Palette
💋 Lipstick: Too Faced Melted Matte Lipstick in “Sell Out”

This timeless look proves beauty has no age and is perfect for weddings and special occasions! 🌸

📹 Watch the reel now and tell us which product you’ll be adding to your cart during the Up to 60% Off sale on Nykaa! 🛍️

✨ Day 1 of My Professional Makeup Course: A Journey of Learning and Growth! ✨

Today was all about setting a strong foundation—literally and figuratively! 💄 We started with warm introductions, explored the science of color theory, and analyzed face shapes in depth. I also demonstrated a flawless mature skin makeup look, which had everyone taking notes! 📝

The most fulfilling part? Guiding my talented students as they practiced each step—perfecting techniques, clicking stunning pictures, and mastering the art of precision. Some of these artists have been in the industry for over 13 years, and seeing them refine their skills today was incredible. 🌟

It’s moments like these, where visible progress happens in just one day, that remind me why I love teaching. Day 1 set the tone for an exciting journey ahead, and I can’t wait to see what we accomplish next! 💕

What was your biggest “aha” moment in class today? Comment below! 👇

This is my go-to skincare routine to keep my skin soft, hydrated, and glowing every night. ✨ I start with the @loccitaneindia Divine Cleansing Balm Makeup remover because it gently melts away makeup without stripping my skin’s natural moisture—leaving it hydrated and refreshed.

Used the @simplynam.beauty towel to remove the balm💕

Next, the Face wash powder with Azuki Beans & Koji Rice from @claycobeauty has become a favorite. It’s a powder cleanser that brightens my face and gives me a natural glow after every wash.

For moisturization, I rely on Emolene, a hidden gem available at pharmacies only. Even with my combination-oily skin, this cream works wonders year-round, improving my skin texture and keeping it balanced.

Finally, I seal in the hydration with the @laneige_in Lip Glowy Balm in shade “Berry”—a must-have for me! After using it for months, my lips have stayed soft and hydrated, even in winter—no cracking whatsoever. 💋

These products are a staple in my nighttime routine, and they’ve made a visible difference in my skin’s health and texture. 🧖‍♀️

What’s your go-to skincare product that you can’t do without? Tell me in the comments!

latestPosts.caption:
Here’s why👇🏼

	1.	Undervaluing my services –
In 2025, I will try to no longer compromise my rates to meet anyone’s budget or offer major discounts. I believe that my clients will recognize that the quality of my work reflects the investment they make.
	2.	Ignoring my personal time –
Personal time is essential for a balanced life. I won’t allow work to overtake my personal life, ensuring that I can recharge and spend quality time with family and friends.
	3.	Working on brand deals without contracts – Everything will be written, confirmed, and professional.
In 2025, I will no longer work with brands or collaborators without clear, professional contracts in place.
	4.	Accommodating unrealistic expectations –
I will set clear expectations with my clients and colleagues, and won’t compromise my skills or time to meet unrealistic demands.
	5.	Taking on projects that don’t align with my goals – In 2025, I’m focusing only on projects that align with my career vision as a bridal makeup artist. I’ll no longer take on side projects that detract from my expertise in bridal makeup.
	6.	Overcommitting to collaborations –
I’ll be more selective with collaborations in 2025. Rather than overcommitting to every opportunity, I will prioritize only those that align with my brand, values, and long-term goals.
	7.	Posting without purpose –
Every piece of content I share will have a purpose. Whether it’s showcasing my work, educating my audience, or engaging with my community, my posts will be intentional and valuable.
	8.	Taking unpaid collaborations –
I will no longer accept unpaid collaborations in 2025. Everything will be professional, and I’ll ensure that all partnerships are mutually beneficial.
	9.	Ignoring my physical and mental health – 
I will prioritize my physical and mental well-being this year. A happy, healthy artist is essential for delivering the best results for my clients.

Which of these points resonates with you the most? Let me know in the comments!
